      "writtenOn": "2019-08-26T19:22:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not the copy encoder that goes in here. It\u0027s the CommandBuffer that the copy encoder\nproduces when done. The idea is to reserve a spot for it before we append the drawing CBs \nthat will use the copied resources.",
      "parentUuid": "5ac9879c_0832ef76",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "b5101323cc32bf95b803bf89311be901f81f0518",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9146407a_08c26e4e",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-26T19:42:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I guess then my question is why not just push back the copyEconders CommandBuffer in flush? Is there some benefit to making sure the copy command buffer is always first? You are always doing a push_back of nullptr at the end of flush anyways.",
      "parentUuid": "cf2fc0d6_293e03df",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "b5101323cc32bf95b803bf89311be901f81f0518",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8c6609f1_16bf785c",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 5290
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-26T20:06:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, the copy CB has to be first, otherwise I\u0027m pretty sure the draws will be invalid (they\u0027ll be drawing with stale data).\n\nAll of the CBs are submitted in a single submit call, which I found was a sizeable win on Metal, for example.",
      "parentUuid": "9146407a_08c26e4e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "b5101323cc32bf95b803bf89311be901f81f0518",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2c5e192e_6a59a8ce",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T14:24:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I guess what seems a little dangerous to me is that there is no code in the GrDawn* backend that seems to be enforcing that copies have to occur before all draws. Like theoretically I can send to the GrDawnGpu the series of commands:\n\n1) appendCommandBuffer from GrDawnOpsRenderPass that includes a draw that samples Tex1\n2) onWritePixels which uploads data to Tex1\n3) appendCommandBuffer from GrDawnOpsRenderPass that includes a draw that samples Tex1\n\nIf the copy that will happen in onWritePixels is moved before command buffer submitted in 1) then you are going to draw wrong there. This is a situation that can happen when we have draws that have inline uploads to textures.\n\nAlso another example is:\n\n1) Draw to RT1\n2) Do dst copy of RT1 to tex1\n3) Draw to RT1 sampling tex1 for blend.\n\nHow do you make sure the writes from 1) happen before the copy in 2)",
      "parentUuid": "8c6609f1_16bf785c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "b5101323cc32bf95b803bf89311be901f81f0518",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d2db4d0c_e43421b1",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 5290
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T15:04:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s an interesting point. I assumed that callers would be explicitly doing a flush() in \norder to ensure that previously-queued work was completed.\n\nDo you know if there\u0027s a test that exercises that call sequence?\n\nIf not, could I write one with just Skia calls, or would I have to make Ganesh calls to do it?",
      "parentUuid": "2c5e192e_6a59a8ce",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "b5101323cc32bf95b803bf89311be901f81f0518",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e221beed_c709ecbc",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T15:36:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So the first example I gave you\u0027d have to trigger an inline upload to occur. I\u0027m not sure what tests hit that. At one point the magnify image filter GM would hit it, but I\u0027m not sure if it does any more. Your best bet is to run through all the gms and break on this function call, https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/skia/src/gpu/GrOpsRenderPass.h?dr\u003dCSs\u0026q\u003dgropsrender\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d67\n\nFor the second example, I think running any of the xfermodes[2,3] gms should cause a dst copy to happen (assuming you don\u0027t have advanced blend extensions or some sort of framebuffer fetch type support).\n\nIn both cases I\u0027m pretty sure we don\u0027t trigger a flush cause we assume the GPU backends will execute the commands in the order they are passed in (or an equivalent ordering).",
      "parentUuid": "d2db4d0c_e43421b1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
